jsDoc.doc: Options on a {@link PickRequest}.

Overrides the random distribution for this request. The output should be in
range for the request.

Picks an integer, given a source of random numbers.

The range is unspecified (given by context).
A source of random signed 32-bit integers.
A generated value and the picks that were used to generate it.

Picks an integer in the given range.

A minimum implementation will just call next(), but it can also substitute a
different PickRequest, such as one with a narrower range.

A function that generates a value, given some picks.

The result should be deterministic, depending only on what `pick` returns.

It may throw {@link Pruned} to indicate that generation failed for the
current pick sequence. (For example, due to filtering.)

Generates a value given a PickRequest, an Arbitrary, or some other PickSet.

Throws {@link Pruned} if no value can be generated, perhaps due to filtering.
Options for {@link PickFunction}.

A function that initializes middleware to respond to PickRequests.

Multiple attempts may be needed to generate a value. The middle() function
will be called once before each attempt.

Filters the generated value.

If it returns false, the pick function may either try a different value or
throw {@link Pruned}.

The maximum number of times to try to generate a value when filtering.
(Default: 1000.)

A set of possible values that may be generated.

(Or perhaps a multiset. PickSets may generate the same value in more than one
way.)
A short label to use in error messsages about this PickSet
Generates a member of this set, given a source of picks.

Specifies a record to be generated.

Each field will be independently generated.

Creates a PickRequest where {@link PickRequest.random} chooses 0 or 1
with the given probability.

Requests a safe, non-negative integer in a given range.

The reply may be any number within range, chosen either deterministically or
randomly.

When picking randomly, the {@link random} function implements the requested
probability distribution.

Constructs a request an integer in a given range.

The range must be over non-negative integers and have at at least one
choice: min <= max.

If no bias is provided, {@link random} implements a uniform distribution.

The function to call when picking randomly.

The output is assumed to satisfy {@link PickRequest.inRange}.
Returns true if the given number satisfies this request.
Returns the number of possible replies for this request.
Describes the request's range, for debugging.

A set of values that can be generated on demand.

Every Arbitrary contains a {@link default} value. Some Arbitraries define
{@link maxSize}, providing an upper bound on how many values they can generate.
Initializer for a subclass that generates the same values as another Arbitrary.
Initializes an Arbitrary, given a callback function.
Initializes a callback or another Arbitrary.
A short string describing this Arbitrary, for use in error messages.

Returns a bound function that can be used to generate values of this
Arbitrary.

(Satisfies the {@link PickSet} interface. Not normally called directly.)

An upper bound on the number of values that this Arbitrary can generate.
(Only available for some small sets.)

Creates a new Arbitrary by mapping each example to a new value. (The
examples are in the same order as in the original.)
Creates a new Arbitrary by filtering out values.

tags.name: accept
tags.doc:
a function that returns true if the value should be kept. It
must allow at least one value through.
if no value can be found that passes the filter.

jsDoc.doc:
Creates a new Arbitrary that maps each example to another Arbitrary and
then picks from it.

(This method is provided because it's traditional, but in most cases,
{@link Arbitrary.from} with a callback is more flexible.)
Returns a new Arbitrary with a different label.

Creates a function that always returns this Arbitrary.

(Useful when optional arguments might be added later.)
A short string describing this Arbitrary, for debugging.
Converts a {@link PickRequest} to an Arbitrary.
Creates an Arbitrary from a {@link PickCallback}, or an array of examples.
Creates an Arbitrary from a {@link PickRequest}, a {@link PickCallback}, or an array of examples.

Creates an Arbitrary that returns one of the given items. The first one
will be the default.

The items are returned as-is, without being cloned. If they are mutable,
this might result in unexpected side effects.

Consider using {@link from} to generate a new instance of mutable objects
each time.
Creates an arbitrary that picks one of the given arbitaries and then returns it.
Creates an Arbitrary for a record with the given shape.
The symbols needed to define a new {@linkcode Arbitrary}.
